  <h2 class="teaser-title"><a href="/diy-new-york-city/subway-updates-smstxt-msg" title="Subway updates via SMS/txt msg">
    Subway updates via SMS/txt msg</a></h2>

  <div class="meta">
          <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/users/reconfigure" title="View user profile.">reconfigure</a> on 3 December 2010 - 11:46pm to <a href="/node/17">DIY New York City</a>.</div>
              <div class="terms"><ul class="links inline"><li  class="first taxonomy_term_11"><a href="/category/approach/mobile-apps" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_11">mobile apps</a></li>
<li  class="taxonomy_term_15"><a href="/taxonomy/term/15" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_15">New York City</a></li>
<li  class="taxonomy_term_5"><a href="/category/topic/public-transportation" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_5">public transportation</a></li>
<li  class="taxonomy_term_383"><a href="/category/additional-tags/sms" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_383">sms</a></li>
<li  class="taxonomy_term_350"><a href="/category/additional-tags/subway" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_350">subway</a></li>
<li  class="last taxonomy_term_384"><a href="/category/additional-tags/txtmsg" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_384">txtmsg</a></li>
</ul></div>
      </div>

  <div class="content clear-block">
        <p>You can now check on subway updates by sending "txtnyc" (space) "subup" to 368-638. There is no need for any kind of registration or fancy-phone.</p>
<p>They are the most recent updates I'm aware of (test it yourself, I have) and the fastest/most convenient way to access it.</p>
  </div>

