<div id="node-691" class="node">

  <h2 class="teaser-title"><a href="/diycity-main-group/would-you-want-apps-contest-your-city-i-want-hear-you" title="Would you want an apps contest in your city?  I want to hear from you">
    Would you want an apps contest in your city?  I want to hear from you</a></h2>

  <div class="meta">
          <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/users/john-geraci" title="View user profile.">John Geraci</a> on 19 November 2010 - 3:15pm to <a href="/node/16">DIYcity Main Group</a>.</div>
          </div>

  <div class="content clear-block">
        <p>I'm thinking through this idea for <a href="http://diycity.org/diycity-main-group/question-diycity-discussions-you-weigh">an apps contest for everywhere</a> a bit more, and would love to hear from people in cities outside of NYC, D.C. and Portland (where apps contests are already happening).  That includes cities in the U.S. as well as cities outside of the U.S.  </p>
<p>Would you be interested in seeing an apps contest in your city?  In Amsterdam?  In Paris?  In Los Angeles?  In Philadelphia?  </p>
<p>If so, drop me a line at geraci at gmail dot com.  I want to chat.  </p>
<p>Or you can reply to <a href="http://diycity.org/discussions/question-anyone-and-everyone-weigh">the thread in the Discussions group</a> .  Or you can <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/apps-for-everywhere">join the Google Group</a> that I set up yesterday to talk about this.</p>
<p>Thanks!</p>
<p>John</p>
  </div>

  <div class="node-links"><ul class="links inline"><li  class="first last comment_forbidden"><span class="comment_forbidden"><a href="/user/login?destination=comment/reply/691%2523comment-form">Login</a> or <a href="/user/register?destination=comment/reply/691%2523comment-form">register</a> to post comments</span></li>
